PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study found that husbands of employed women reported slightly lower levels of job satisfaction, marital adjustment, and quality of life than husbands of housewives. Husbands' time commitment to work and satisfaction with childcare were found to mediate the effect of wives' employment on husbands' job satisfaction and marital adjustment, respectively.
AB  - This study found that husbands of employed women reported slightly lower levels of job satisfaction, marital adjustment, and quality of life than husbands of housewives. Husbands' time commitment to work and satisfaction with childcare were found to mediate the effect of wives' employment on husbands' job satisfaction and marital adjustment, respectively.
