JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 202
EP  - 212
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examines Williamson's (1975) concept of opportunism in relations between farm and power equipment dealers and their primary supplier organization. Results from a national survey generally support hypotheses predicting that dealer opportunism will be negatively related to dealer dependence on a primary supplier and positively related to supplier control over dealer decisions.
AB  - This study examines Williamson's (1975) concept of opportunism in relations between farm and power equipment dealers and their primary supplier organization. Results from a national survey generally support hypotheses predicting that dealer opportunism will be negatively related to dealer dependence on a primary supplier and positively related to supplier control over dealer decisions.
